-- The libllama-side bailout that this spec is INDEPENDENT of:
--   ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:608-616
--     — can_reuse_graph; the n_stream > 1 early-return at line 616.
--       This spec models what the backend offers; the bailout decides
--       whether to ask. Tier 2 work in PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md drops
--       the bailout; the contracts here remain unchanged.
--
-- Black-box helpers used inline in the system-wide invariants
-- (not in `deferred` per project convention — they have no separate
-- .allium spec):
--   CudaContexts, CgraphNodes, CgraphInputsAt,
--   MatchingCacheEntryFor, NodePropertiesAt, CacheActionFor,
--   TopologyKeyInCache, SomeEntryEvictedBeforeInsert.
--
-- Test infrastructure to drive from this spec via allium:propagate
-- (planned as P0.B.S4 in PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md):
--   - Property test that submits two cgraphs with the same
--     op-sequence and different ne dimensions; asserts the second
--     submission takes the exec_update path (not instantiate_then_
--     reuse). PASS on HEAD.
--   - Property test that submits a cgraph with one GGML_OP_VIEW
--     node whose src->data is permuted between calls; asserts the
--     second submission still takes the reuse_unchanged path
--     (the address change is absorbed by the VIEW tolerance).
--     PASS on HEAD.
--   - Property test that submits the same op-sequence with one
--     node's dst dtype changed F16 -> F32 between calls; asserts
--     the second submission takes the reinstantiate path (the
--     dtype-strict check forces it). PASS on HEAD.
--   - Property test that submits >128 distinct topology hashes
--     and asserts ctx.cache_size never exceeds 128. PASS on HEAD.

-- ============================================================
-- Related specs
-- ============================================================

-- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium
--   The 4D per-stream KV layout. ITS PerStreamDispatch contract is
--   what Tier 3 will satisfy; THIS spec is the backend mechanism
--   Tier 2 depends on while still running per-stream dispatch.
--   The OQ-3 in that spec ("graph cache invalidation under K/V
--   shape change") is answered by DtypeStrictness +
--   AddressToleranceScopedToViewCpy here: the K/V tensor shape
--   change from 3D to 4D invalidates every cached graph on the
--   first post-change decode (different ne -> exec_update path
--   -> rewrite of fingerprints), no manual flush needed.
--
-- specs/kv-cache/per_stream_read_view_patching.allium (forthcoming,
-- P0.B.S1.b)
--   The Tier 2 patching contract. THAT spec extends
--   update_cache_copies to also patch the read-view src_address
--   in llm_build_kqv. The mechanism it depends on is
--   ViewCpyAddressTolerance.ViewCpySrcAddressMismatchToleratedOnVcpy
--   here: VIEW src_address can change between calls without
--   invalidating the cached executable, so the per-stream read
--   view patching does not force a reinstantiate per decode.
--
-- specs/dispatch/unified_stream_dispatch.allium (forthcoming,
-- P0.B.S1.c)
--   The Tier 3 dispatch contract. Under unified dispatch, all
--   active streams share one llama_decode per tick and the
--   topology_hash collapses to one entry per (n_streams, n_kv-
--   bucket) combination. The CapacityBoundedByConfig bound here
--   continues to hold; DtypeStrictness continues to prevent
--   cross-dtype reuse during the transition between dispatch
--   modes.
--
-- specs/scheduler/batch_composition.allium
--   The scheduler-level Bug C closure. Independent of this spec
--   (the cache reuses graphs the scheduler submits; whether the
--   scheduler may submit a mixed batch is governed there). The
--   only cross-cut is DtypeStrictness: if Tier 3 unifies dispatch
--   and a future regression reintroduces mixed-dtype batches, the
--   dtype-strict check will force a reinstantiate every tick —
--   measurable as cache thrash in the probe, not as a wrong
--   output. The spec catches the perf signal before it becomes a
--   correctness signal.
